---
description: Testing workflow guidelines
globs:
  - "tests/**/*.py"
  - "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Before changing logic, inspect current file behavior first.
- Prefer helper tests and mode-module tests before end-to-end tests.
- Prefer local fixture files over live network tests unless explicitly requested.
- After changes, propose one minimal smoke test and one focused unit test.
- If a change affects ffmpeg behavior, naming, ordering, or metadata, mention that explicitly in the test plan.
- Do not claim refactor success without a verification path.
- Prefer behavior-focused tests over implementation-detail tests.
- Do not generate tests only to increase test count.
- Avoid asserting exact internal helper calls unless that interaction is itself important behavior.
- Avoid asserting full log output unless the log content is part of the intended contract.
- Prefer one meaningful test per behavior branch over many near-duplicate tests.
- Use mocking only at external boundaries (ffmpeg, ffprobe, network, filesystem side effects) unless deeper mocking is truly necessary.
- Before adding tests, briefly state what regression each new test is meant to catch.
- Do not run the full test suite after every tiny change unless explicitly asked.
- Prefer running the smallest relevant subset first, then the full suite only at meaningful checkpoints.